summary: Spoiler Alert! Do not read if you have not yet finished TWIA...
title: Spoiler Alert! Do not read if you have not yet finished TWIA...
body:
I decided to address these two messages together, but due to the content, I had to make a spoiler alert for those who have not yet finished Two Weeks In Autumn. I don’t want to spoil it for everyone. Note that should I get anymore messages like this, I may or may not post them, simply because I’m addressing it in this post…

First, thank you to both anons for messaging me! I appreciate your thoughts very much!

To the anon who has lost my trust…Two Weeks In Autumn DID have a happy ending. It was not the ending you expected or wanted maybe, but it was a happy ending. Did Harry and his children live in grief, remaining in sadness only 1 year past her death? No. When you are faced with the death of a close loved one, it is not a matter of moving on, it is a matter of moving forward, and that is what they did. So even though the OFC was no longer in their lives, they were still happy, because they had such wonderful memories of her, and loads of love!

And as for the other anon who suggested an alternate ending…Bruh, color me intrigued!!! Alternate ending, eh? I’ve never written an alternate ending before, but I do love those when a movie provides one. It is something I will consider, although maybe not soon as I’m taking a short break for a few days, then working on music imagines, but I will think on it. Thanks for the suggestion!

I hope that I did not taint your reading of my work by the fact that neither of you, possibly more, enjoyed the ending I chose for this story, but personally…I loved it! I debated for weeks over ending it like this, but it was the only ending in my mind, and I wanted it to be a short and sweet ending, which is why I wrote it as an epilogue, rather than dragging out a full chapter over it. I mapped out two or three different thoughts for endings, but none of them invoked emotions for me except this one.

Thank you for reading, and I hope maybe you will enjoy the next story more! Much love to you! xo

Shelli

body:
From what I read of the reaction for Harry🌸’ Met Gala outfit , 2 genres of ppl hated (or didn’t like his look) :

1) Het harries got shocked, HATED his look 100% , they literally shaking cuz this look was LOUD , very very LOUD

(& from a straight girl point of view, Harry🌸 LOOKED LIKE A BEAUTIFUL LADY, believe me that’s how I saw him & all straight ppl saw him, but the difference is hets didn’t like it at all cuz it means that Harry🌸 isn’t straight )

2)Some gay men didn’t like it cuz they expected more gay look & a carnival theme full of rainbow colours ..

& Here a gay man who noticed the mocking coming from gay men, so he dragged them :

& this a small ex of how many gay men saw Harry🌸 outfit :

To sum up, the criticism came from ppl who saw the outfit too gay and very feminine , and other ppl who saw the outfit not as much gay as they expected or wanted … And that’s exactly the message Harry🌸 wanted to deliver with Harry Lambert & Alessandro Michelle, Harry expressed himself, his personality with a touch of exaggerating and that’s why he is KING of fashion, & that ’s why Harry🌸’ outfit was on point that day)
